Rating: 0
Canned Chile Poblanos, already charred, peeled and sliced into strips are available in Latin grocery stores. We poach the meatballs in boiling lightly salted water with a sprig of mint,thus providing the broth for the soup. In another soup pot sautee chopped onions until they are translucent. Slowly add two cups of pureed tomatoes and stiring slowly cook until they are 'orange' in colour. Carefully add meat balls, and the broth required. Reduce the heat and simmer for 45 minutes. Correct the seasoning. These same meatballs are delicious served in salsa (hot of course) over "arroz a la mexicana." Serve with "bolillos" or freshly made hot tortillas.

