I really liked this soup. It was not greasy -- I used ground sirloin and not ground beef for the meatballs. McCormick makes the Ancho Chili Powder and the only grocery store that carries it in my area is Kroger. I also added a little Chipotle Chili Pepper, too. For the soup, I always sautee my onions till golden (8-10 minutes), then add garlic. I julienned my zucchini and then cut into 1/2" pieces. I also added finely chopped yellow, orange and red bell peppers for color, as well as sliced mushrooms.Great spicy soup and delicious meatballs. As another viewer suggested, corn might add to the soup -- roasted corn, no less!

