Great recipe, though finding the ancho chile powder was hard! Ended up making my own from dried ancho chiles sold at my local hispanic food store. I followed other reviewers suggestions and doubled the rice and added a can of corn - both of which made it a more substantial soup. While this was not a time intensive recipem, if you are short on time, I would use canned green chiles instead of roasting your own poblano and use store bought tortilla strips. Great weeknight meal that I will definitely be making again!

