This was a hearty soup but not heavy  the addition of zucchini really lightened the meatballs. We added a roasted jalapeno to the meatballs and kept some of the poblano strips to throw into the broth mixture. I also toasted the cumin before grinding it which always seems to give a nicer flavor. After sautéing the corn tortilla strips, we sprinkled them with sea salt and added diced avocado to top the soup. Served with tamarind margaritas  it was a lovely way to end the holidays. .

